categories.name: Mammals
categories.description: Animals that typically have fur or hair, give birth to live young, and nurse their offspring with milk.

categories.name: Amphibians
categories.description: Cold-blooded vertebrates that usually lay eggs in water and undergo metamorphosis from aquatic larvae to terrestrial adults.

categories.name: Reptiles
categories.description: Cold-blooded vertebrates characterized by scales, laying eggs on land, and having a lung-based respiratory system.

categories.name: Birds
categories.description: Warm-blooded vertebrates with feathers, beaks, and lay hard-shelled eggs. They are known for their ability to fly.

categories.name: Cats
categories.description: Small carnivorous mammals known for their retractable claws, sharp teeth, and agility. They are popular as pets.

categories.name: Insects
categories.description: Small invertebrates with six legs and typically one or two pairs of wings. They undergo metamorphosis and play vital roles in ecosystems.

categories.name: Fish
categories.description: Aquatic vertebrates with gills, fins, and scales. They breathe through gills and are adapted to life in water.

animals.name: African Elephant
animals.description: The African elephant is the largest land animal on Earth. They are known for their long tusks and distinctive trunk.

animals.name: Bengal Tiger
animals.description: The Bengal tiger is the most numerous tiger subspecies. They are known for their orange fur with black stripes and powerful build.

animals.name: Snow Leopard
animals.habitat: Mountain ranges of Central and South Asia
animals.description: The snow leopard is a large cat native to the mountain ranges of Central and South Asia. It is characterized by its thick fur and spotted coat.

animals.name: Giant Panda
animals.description: The giant panda is a bear native to China. It is known for its distinctive black and white coat and its diet primarily consisting of bamboo.

animals.name: Gorilla
animals.description: Gorillas are the largest living primates. They are ground-dwelling and primarily herbivorous.

animals.name: Red Kangaroo
animals.description: The red kangaroo is the largest kangaroo species. It is known for its distinctive red fur and powerful hind legs, which allow it to hop long distances.

animals.name: Polar Bear
animals.description: The polar bear is a large bear native to the Arctic. It is superbly adapted to its icy habitat with thick fur and a layer of fat for insulation.

animals.name: Komodo Dragon
animals.habitat: Indonesian islands of Komodo, Rinca, Flores, and Gili Motang
animals.description: The Komodo dragon is the world's largest lizard. It is a fierce predator with a venomous bite and can be found in the Indonesian islands.

animals.name: Blue Whale
animals.description: The blue whale is the largest animal on Earth. They are marine mammals and feed primarily on krill. They are known for their immense size and distinctive blue-gray color.

animals.name: African Lion
animals.description: The African lion is a large carnivorous cat known for its mane. It is a keystone species in its ecosystem, playing a crucial role in maintaining the balance of the African savanna.

animals.name: Amazon Rainforest Frog
animals.description: The Amazon Rainforest Frog, also known as poison dart frogs, are small colorful frogs native to the Amazon Rainforest. Some species possess toxins used by indigenous tribes for hunting.

animals.name: Siberian Tiger
animals.habitat: Russian Far East, Northeast China, and possibly North Korea
animals.description: The Siberian Tiger, also known as the Amur Tiger, is the largest cat species and primarily found in the forests of eastern Russia. Poaching and habitat loss are the main threats to its survival.

animals.name: Galapagos Giant Tortoise
animals.description: The Galapagos Giant Tortoise is one of the largest tortoise species in the world. They are native to the Galapagos Islands and are known for their long lifespans, sometimes exceeding 100 years.

animals.name: Bald Eagle
animals.description: The Bald Eagle is a bird of prey found in North America, primarily near large bodies of open water. It is the national bird and symbol of the United States.

animals.name: Pangolin
animals.description: Pangolins are unique mammals covered in protective keratin scales. They are often poached for their scales, which are used in traditional Chinese medicine.

animals.name: Sloth
animals.description: Sloths are slow-moving mammals found in the rainforests of Central and South America. They spend most of their time hanging upside down from trees.

animals.name: Panda Ant
animals.description: The Panda Ant is a species of wingless wasp found in South America. Its black and white coloration resembles that of a panda, hence its name.

animals.name: Australian Platypus
animals.description: The Australian Platypus is a unique mammal that lays eggs and is native to eastern Australia. It has a duck-like bill, webbed feet, and a beaver-like tail.

animals.name: Green Sea Turtle
animals.description: The Green Sea Turtle is one of the largest sea turtles and is found in tropical and subtropical oceans worldwide. They are herbivores, feeding on seagrasses and algae.

animals.name: Reticulated Python
animals.description: The Reticulated Python is one of the largest snake species and is found in the jungles and forests of Southeast Asia. It is known for its beautifully patterned scales.

animals.name: Golden Lion Tamarin
animals.description: The Golden Lion Tamarin is a small monkey with a striking golden mane. It is native to the Atlantic coastal forests of Brazil and is critically endangered due to habitat loss.

animals.name: Quetzal
animals.description: The Quetzal is a colorful bird native to the cloud forests of Central America. It is known for its vibrant plumage and long tail feathers.

animals.name: Coelacanth
animals.description: The Coelacanth is a prehistoric fish that was thought to be extinct until it was rediscovered in the 20th century. It inhabits deep underwater caves.

animals.name: Axolotl
animals.description: The Axolotl is a unique salamander known for its regenerative abilities. It is native to the Xochimilco lake complex in Mexico and is critically endangered.

animals.name: Serval
animals.description: The Serval is a medium-sized wild cat native to the grasslands of Africa. It is known for its long legs, which help it hunt in tall grass.

animals.name: Sunda Flying Lemur
animals.description: The Sunda Flying Lemur, also known as the Sunda Colugo, is not a lemur and cannot fly. It is a gliding mammal native to the forests of Southeast Asia.

animals.name: Giant Otter
animals.description: The Giant Otter is a large otter species native to South America. It is known for its long body, dense fur, and social behavior.

animals.name: African Wild Dog
animals.description: The African Wild Dog, also known as the painted wolf, is a highly social carnivore native to sub-Saharan Africa. It is endangered due to habitat loss and human conflict.

animals.name: Red Panda
animals.description: The Red Panda is a small arboreal mammal native to the eastern Himalayas and southwestern China. It is known for its distinctive red fur and bushy tail.

animals.name: Monarch Butterfly
animals.description: The Monarch Butterfly is known for its distinctive orange and black wings. It is famous for its long-distance seasonal migration in North America.

animals.name: Cheetah
animals.habitat: Savannas of Africa and parts of Iran
animals.description: The cheetah is the fastest land animal, capable of reaching speeds up to 70 mph in short bursts. It is found in the savannas of Africa and parts of Iran.

animals.name: Mountain Gorilla
animals.description: The mountain gorilla is a subspecies of the eastern gorilla found in the mountain forests of Africa. It is one of the most endangered apes in the world.

treeCategories.name: Deciduous Trees
treeCategories.description: Deciduous trees shed their leaves annually, usually in the fall.

treeCategories.name: Coniferous Trees
treeCategories.description: Coniferous trees bear cones and have needle-like or scale-like leaves that are typically evergreen.

treeCategories.name: Tropical Trees
treeCategories.description: Tropical trees thrive in warm climates and are often found in rainforests or tropical regions.

treeCategories.name: Temperate Trees
treeCategories.description: Temperate trees grow in regions with moderate climates and distinct seasons.

treeCategories.name: Fruit Trees
treeCategories.description: Fruit trees produce edible fruits and are cultivated for their fruits rather than timber.

treeCategories.name: Palm Trees
treeCategories.description: Palm trees are characterized by their unbranched stems and large, fan-shaped leaves. They are common in tropical and subtropical regions.

treeCategories.name: Ornamental Trees
treeCategories.description: Ornamental trees are cultivated for their aesthetic value, such as colorful foliage, flowers, or unique shapes.

treeCategories.name: Native Trees
treeCategories.description: Native trees are indigenous to a particular region or habitat and play a crucial role in local ecosystems.

treeCategories.name: Exotic Trees
treeCategories.description: Exotic trees are non-native species introduced to new regions. They may have ecological impacts on local ecosystems.

treeCategories.name: Urban Trees
treeCategories.description: Urban trees grow in urban environments and provide various benefits, including shade, air purification, and habitat for urban wildlife.

treeCategories.name: Forest Trees
treeCategories.description: Forest trees are found in forested areas and play a significant role in maintaining ecosystem health and biodiversity.

treeCategories.name: Mountain Trees
treeCategories.description: Mountain trees grow at high altitudes and are adapted to harsh mountainous conditions, such as cold temperatures and strong winds.

treeCategories.name: Wetland Trees
treeCategories.description: Wetland trees grow in marshes, swamps, and other wetland habitats. They are adapted to periodically flooded conditions.

treeCategories.name: Drought-Resistant Trees
treeCategories.description: Drought-resistant trees are adapted to arid climates and can survive with minimal water.

treeCategories.name: Shade Trees
treeCategories.description: Shade trees have dense canopies that provide relief from the sun's heat and are commonly planted for landscaping and urban cooling.

treeCategories.name: Alley Trees
treeCategories.description: Alley trees are planted along streets or avenues and contribute to urban greening and aesthetics.

treeCategories.name: Boundary Trees
treeCategories.description: Boundary trees mark property lines or boundaries and may have cultural or historical significance.

treeCategories.name: Heritage Trees
treeCategories.description: Heritage trees are old, significant trees with historical, cultural, or ecological importance.

treeCategories.name: Fire-Resistant Trees
treeCategories.description: Fire-resistant trees are adapted to withstand wildfires and play a role in fire ecology.

treeCategories.name: Windbreak Trees
treeCategories.description: Windbreak trees are planted to reduce wind erosion, protect crops, and create microclimates.

trees.name: Oak
trees.description: A common deciduous tree known for its strong wood and distinctive lobed leaves.

trees.name: Maple
trees.description: Maples are deciduous trees known for their vibrant autumn foliage and sap used in maple syrup production.

trees.name: Birch
trees.description: Birch trees have distinctive white bark and delicate leaves, often found in temperate forests.

trees.name: Pine
trees.description: Pines are coniferous trees with needle-like leaves and produce pine cones.

trees.name: Spruce
trees.description: Spruces are coniferous trees known for their pyramidal shape and sharp needles.

trees.name: Fir
trees.description: Firs are coniferous trees with soft needles and upright cones.

trees.name: Palm
trees.description: Palms are tropical trees with fan-shaped leaves and often found in beach or rainforest environments.

trees.name: Mango
trees.description: Mango trees are tropical fruit trees known for their sweet and juicy fruits.

trees.name: Banana
trees.description: Banana trees produce clusters of edible bananas and thrive in warm, humid climates.

trees.name: European Beech
trees.description: A temperate deciduous tree with smooth gray bark and oval leaves.

trees.name: Japanese Maple
trees.description: An ornamental tree with delicate foliage, popular in temperate gardens.

trees.name: Douglas Fir
trees.description: A large coniferous tree native to North America, valued for its timber.

trees.name: Apple
trees.description: Apple trees produce crisp, sweet fruits and are widely cultivated in orchards.

trees.name: Orange
trees.description: Orange trees produce round, citrus fruits prized for their juice.

trees.name: Cherry
trees.description: Cherry trees produce small, sweet fruit and are popular for home gardens.

trees.name: Coconut Palm
trees.description: Coconut palms produce coconuts and are commonly found in tropical coastal areas.

trees.name: Date Palm
trees.description: Date palms produce sweet, edible dates and are cultivated in arid regions.

trees.name: Sago Palm
trees.description: Sago palms have feathery leaves and produce starchy seeds used in cooking.

trees.name: Japanese Cherry Blossom
trees.description: Known for its beautiful pink blossoms, often seen in gardens and parks.

trees.name: Redbud
trees.description: Redbuds are small ornamental trees with pink or purple flowers in spring.

trees.name: Dogwood
trees.description: Dogwoods have showy flowers and colorful foliage, popular in landscaping.

trees.name: California Redwood
trees.description: Native to California, redwoods are the tallest trees in the world.

trees.name: White Pine
trees.description: A common native pine tree in eastern North America, valued for its straight trunk and soft wood.

trees.name: Bald Cypress
trees.description: Native to swamps of the southeastern United States, known for its 'knees' and buttressed trunk.

trees.name: Eucalyptus
trees.description: Native to Australia, eucalyptus trees are now grown in many regions for their fast growth and aromatic leaves.

trees.name: Norfolk Island Pine
trees.description: Native to Norfolk Island, these conifers are often grown as ornamentals in other regions.

trees.name: Ash
trees.description: Ash trees are deciduous with compound leaves and distinctive black buds.

trees.name: Willow
trees.description: Willows have long, narrow leaves and pendulous branches, often found near water.

trees.name: Elm
trees.description: Elms are deciduous trees with serrated leaves and a broad, vase-shaped crown.

trees.name: Cedar
trees.description: Cedars are coniferous trees with fragrant wood and scale-like leaves.

trees.name: Hemlock
trees.description: Hemlocks are coniferous trees with flat needles and drooping branches.

trees.name: Juniper
trees.description: Junipers are conifers with needle-like leaves and berry-like cones.

trees.name: Avocado
trees.description: Avocado trees produce creamy, nutrient-rich fruits and are native to Central America.

trees.name: Papaya
trees.description: Papaya trees produce large, tropical fruits with orange flesh and black seeds.

trees.name: Guava
trees.description: Guava trees bear small, round fruits with a fragrant aroma and sweet flavor.

trees.name: Hawthorn
trees.description: Hawthorns are small deciduous trees with thorny branches and clusters of white or pink flowers.

trees.name: Aspen
trees.description: Aspens are fast-growing deciduous trees with shimmering leaves that flutter in the breeze.

trees.name: Sycamore
trees.description: Sycamores have distinctive mottled bark and large, lobed leaves.

trees.name: Lemon
trees.description: Lemon trees produce tart, yellow fruits used in cooking and beverages.

trees.name: Peach
trees.description: Peach trees bear fuzzy-skinned fruits with sweet, juicy flesh.

trees.name: Pear
trees.description: Pear trees produce sweet, crisp fruits that come in various shapes and colors.

trees.name: Areca Palm
trees.description: Areca palms have feathery fronds and produce small, orange fruit.

trees.name: Majesty Palm
trees.description: Majesty palms are popular indoor plants with graceful, arching fronds.

trees.name: Fan Palm
trees.description: Fan palms have large, fan-shaped leaves and are commonly used in landscaping.

trees.name: Magnolia
trees.description: Magnolias are ornamental trees with large, fragrant flowers in shades of white, pink, or purple.

trees.name: Crabapple
trees.description: Crabapples are small, flowering trees with tart fruit often used in jams and jellies.

trees.name: Live Oak
trees.description: Live oaks are evergreen trees with broad, spreading crowns and leathery leaves.

trees.name: Black Cherry
trees.description: Black cherries are native deciduous trees with edible fruits and valuable timber.

trees.name: Catalpa
trees.description: Catalpas are deciduous trees with showy flowers and long, bean-like seed pods.

trees.name: Monkey Puzzle
trees.description: Monkey puzzle trees are evergreen conifers with spiky, overlapping leaves and large, egg-shaped cones.

trees.name: Norfolk Island Hibiscus
trees.description: Norfolk Island hibiscus trees have glossy leaves and large, showy flowers in shades of pink, red, or yellow.

trees.name: London Plane
trees.description: London planes are large deciduous trees often planted in urban areas for their tolerance to pollution and ability to provide shade.

trees.name: Ginkgo
trees.description: Ginkgo trees are known for their unique fan-shaped leaves and resilience to urban conditions.

trees.name: Red Alder
trees.description: Red alders are fast-growing deciduous trees found in forested areas of North America, providing important habitat and nitrogen fixation.

trees.name: Sitka Spruce
trees.description: Sitka spruces are large conifers native to the Pacific Northwest and are valuable timber trees in forest ecosystems.

trees.name: Engelmann Spruce
trees.description: Engelmann spruces are conifers adapted to high-altitude mountain environments, providing habitat and stabilization in rocky terrain.

trees.name: Alpine Fir
trees.description: Alpine firs are evergreen trees that thrive in mountainous regions, tolerating cold temperatures and high winds.

trees.name: Black Gum
trees.description: Black gums, or tupelos, are deciduous trees commonly found in wetland habitats of North America, providing food and habitat for wildlife.

trees.name: Willow Oak
trees.description: Willow oaks are deciduous trees with willow-like leaves and are often found in wetland areas, providing shade and erosion control.

trees.name: Crape Myrtle
trees.description: Crape myrtles are drought-resistant deciduous trees known for their colorful flowers and attractive bark.

trees.name: Texas Ebony
trees.description: Texas ebonies are evergreen trees native to arid regions of Texas and northern Mexico, capable of withstanding extreme drought.

trees.name: Sweetgum
trees.description: Sweetgums are deciduous trees with star-shaped leaves that provide dense shade and are often planted for landscaping.

trees.name: Tulip Tree
trees.description: Tulip trees, or tulip poplars, are large deciduous trees with tulip-like flowers and are prized for their shade and ornamental value.

trees.name: American Elm
trees.description: American elms are tall deciduous trees commonly planted along streets and avenues for their graceful arching branches and vase-like shape.

trees.name: Cedar of Lebanon
trees.description: Cedars of Lebanon are evergreen trees historically planted as boundary markers and valued for their majestic appearance.

trees.name: Angel Oak
trees.description: Angel oaks are massive live oaks with sprawling branches and are considered cultural and historical landmarks.

trees.name: Yew Tree
trees.description: Yew trees have dark green foliage and red berries, often associated with ancient religious sites and folklore.

trees.name: California Redbud
trees.description: California redbuds are drought-resistant trees native to California and are valued for their springtime display of pink flowers.

trees.name: Madrone
trees.description: Madrones are drought-resistant evergreen trees with striking red bark and white flowers.

trees.name: Eastern Red Cedar
trees.description: Eastern red cedars are windbreak trees commonly planted to protect crops and property from strong winds and erosion.

trees.name: Black Locust
trees.description: Black locusts are fast-growing trees planted as windbreaks and for their nitrogen-fixing ability in poor soils.
